{"experiment_id": "synthetic_benign", "epoch": 15, "role": "user", "artifact_class": "Commit", "identifier": ["microsoft", "vscode", "0dcd9bc7d3c0deaf25480b3793e67c9bb9457d5c"], "url": "https://github.com/microsoft/vscode/commit/0dcd9bc7d3c0deaf25480b3793e67c9bb9457d5c", "semantic_text": "Merge pull request #60 from RHILIUS/Exequiel\n\n\ud83d\udee0\ufe0f Agila Transport Patch v1.0.0 \u2014 \"UI Standards Overhaul\"\nRelease Date: 2025-06-04\n\n\ud83c\udfa8 UI Overhaul: Now Aligned with Agila Standards!\nWe've brought the entire app's visual language up to spec. Consistency, clarity, and cleanliness are now at the core of your experience.\n\n\ud83d\udd18 Button Redesigns\nStandardized all button styles across the platform.\n\nIntroduced .addButton, .editBtn, and .deleteBtn with:\n\nUnified padding, fonts, and color schemes.\nSmooth hover transitions.\nIcon support with scaling animations.\n\ud83d\udd0d Search Field Refined\n\nAdded icon support using absolute positioning for a more intuitive look.\n\nPolished spacing, padding, and placeholder handling.\n\nStyled .searchInput for full consistency with dropdowns.\n\n\u2b07\ufe0f Dropdown Styling\n\nNew .sortSelect dropdown:\n\nRounded corners and clean borders.\n\nFont and padding adjusted to match buttons and inputs.\n\nUnified height across toolbars.\n\n\ud83c\udd95 SweetAlert2 (Swal) Integration\n\nAll modals (confirmation, success, and error) now use Swal2 for:\nDeletion confirmations.\nError alerts with rich messages.\nSuccess feedback after actions (e.g., deleting routes or assignments).\n\ud83e\ude84 Modals Polished\n\nLegacy Bootstrap modals are being phased out.\nNew modals conform to spacing, rounded corners, and font standards.\n\ud83e\udde0 Font Standardization\n\nApp-wide adoption of 'Open Sans', sans-serif.\nText elements, tables, and modals now follow the same font and sizing rules for clarity and uniformity.\n\ud83d\udce6 Other UI Improvements\n\nAdjusted table border-radius with customizable corner options.\n.center-box, .wideCard, and .toolbar classes now better aligned.\nEnhanced table row hover feedback for better UX.\n\ud83e\uddf9 Code & UX Cleanup\n\nRemoved duplicate Swal handling in async calls (ensuring .isConfirmed is always checked).\nReplaced hardcoded alerts with Swal to maintain UI cohesion.\nMade delete and edit operations less error-prone with better async/await handling.", "semantic_meaning": null, "semantic_ref": null, "semantic_label": "benign", "semantic_content_type": "real", "timestamp": 1611045963.0}
